    "content": "<h1>CRISPUS</h1><p>A leader of the Jewish synagogue in Corinth. Crispus and everyone in his household became followers of Jesus during the apostle Paul&apos;s 18-month missionary visit to the city (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8,Acts18:11\">Acts 18:8, 11</a>). Paul mentioned Crispus as one of the few people he personally baptized in Corinth (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:14\">1&nbsp;Corinthians 1:14</a>).</p>",
